title: Marquez on pole for Australian MotoGP
text:
PHILLIP ISLAND: Spain's Marc Marquez on Saturday took pole position for this weekend's Australian MotoGP at Phillip Island.
The defending world champion, on a Repsol Honda , clocked a fastest lap of one minute 28.364 seconds to start on the inside of the grid for Sunday's race.
Italian Ducati rider Andrea Iannone was second ahead of Spain's Movistar Yamaha star Jorge Lorenzo.
